rComments: I took MUS3905. At first, I thought he was a little intimidating, but then I realized that's just the way he shows his enthusiasm for things. I didn't like the way he answered a question one time, but he picked up on that and saught me out after and explained himself. I really appreciated that.
When I was really, really down on myself he encouraged me and helped me find my confidence. He cared about people who cared.
Brilliant musician and artist. A little frustrated by the end of the year, and showed it. It wasn't his fault though. Has no tolerance for fakers.
good prof, good music. kinda lame class but not cause of him.
Fabulous conductor and great choral instructor. Very intense and passionate man. Loves the music he teaches.
